<br>
<br>
Using 8 SSRB's as a first stage will get you 5000 tons off the ground.  You want to launch the full 5000, too, because if you don't your unthrottled solids will rack up HUGE g-forces right before they burn out.<br>
<br>
So, you get 5000 tons off the ground and flying.  I would then use a liquid fueled second stage, ignited in the air, fueled with kerosene and LOX for Isp of 300-ish or the even denser kerosene and OF2 for smaller tankage and Isp of 360-ish.  Although, to be frank, efficiency is not a worry here, cheap is.<br>
<br>
Put 3000 tons into this second stage, burn it for 300 or 400 seconds or so and voila, you should be well clear of the atmosphere with a 2000 ton Orion.  It WON'T be in orbit at this point, I don't even have to run the numbers to know you are nowhere near 9km/sec deltaV with this rig, but you will be plenty high and way over the ocean, so simply start blowing off yer bombs.  Pulse good and slow, maybe one shot every 5 seconds, so as to keep things simple.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Pros?  Simple tech, well known.<br>
<br>
Cons?  HUGE, expensive due to the SRB's, REALLY HUGE.<br>
<br>
